Example code:

```
typedef enum logic
{
    POSITIVE = 1'h0,
    NEGATIVE = 1'h1
} polarity;

typedef struct packed
{
    logic polarity;
} foo;
```

With `master` from a few moments ago:

```
❯ verilator --version
 rev v5.026-4-g833df6d9e

❯ verilator --cc main.sv
%Error: main.sv:9:11: syntax error, unexpected TYPE-IDENTIFIER
    9 |     logic polarity;
      |           ^~~~~~~~
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
```

This seems similar to #2195 ? Probably not a good idea to write code like this, but Questa allows it at least.
